In a letter from Lord Bauer, House of Lords, Westminster SW1, Lord
Bauer expressed his concerns that the international community may be
encouraging Third World countries to default on debts.

Lord Bauer writes "The debts of African countries have often been
canceled or rescheduled, frequently several times for the same
country."

In expressing his views on some causes of poverty he writes "To harp
on alleged external causes of Third World poverty diverts attention
from the real factors behind this poverty which are domestic, and
thereby from the possibilities of addressing these." He suggests that
some causes may include government dependence on precarious
subsistence production.</SUM>

<SUM
